<H3> <TI>   To Meet With Argentine President </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    To Meet With Argentine President </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   FL1304013794 Havana Radio Reloj Network in Spanish 1932 GMT 
12 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL1304013794 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Radio Reloj Network </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Foreign Minister Roberto Robaina, who is visiting 
several South American nations, will meet on 13 April with 
President Carlos Saul Menem at the beginning of a two-day 
official trip to Argentina. Robaina stopped briefly in Argentina 
over the weekend and met with Argentine Foreign Minister Guido 
di Tella to discuss international and bilateral issues. Robaina 
already visited Uruguay and Peru. 
  According to the official agenda, Robaina will meet on 13 
April with Menem following a meeting with the plenum of the 
Argentine Senate, headed by Eduardo Menem. Robaina also will 
conduct a courtesy visit to interim Foreign Minister Fernando 
Petrella since Di Tella is abroad, and will lay a wreath at the 
monument of national liberator Jose de San Martin. Also on 13 
April, the Buenos Aires City Council will confer on Robaina the 
title of Illustrious Visitor. 
  On 14 April, Robaina will give an address on investment and 
trade with Cuba to members of Argentina's Chamber of Commerce 
and Industry. Robaina will also meet with Deputy Economy 
Minister Carlos Sanchez and will conduct a second work meeting 
at the Argentine Foreign Ministry. 
  Robaina's trip to Argentina will conclude with a public 
event 
organized by friendship and solidarity groups, which demand 
respect for Cuba's self-determination and lifting of the U.S. 
blockade of Cuba. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

