<F P=102>   FL1204133094 Havana Radio Rebelde Network in Spanish 0900 
GMT 12 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL1204133094 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Radio Rebelde Network </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] On concluding an overall control visit to the 
Committees for the Defense of the Revolution [CDR] in Sancti 
Spiritus, Division General Sixto Batista Santana, national 
coordinator of the CDR and member of the Cuban Communist Party 
Central Committee, said that the moral and political status of 
the people of Sancti Spiritus is satisfactory. 
  Gen. Batista added that the CDR members resolutely support 
the need to adopt measures to streamline the country's finances. 
He also stressed the province's effort to fulfill the current 
sugar harvest plan. 
  Gen. Batista said that Sancti Spiritus has increased the 
flow 
of currency into the country through tourism and through the 
efficient work of the people. 

