<H3> <TI>   Sugar Minister Stresses Importance of Efforts </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Sugar Minister Stresses Importance of Efforts </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   FL1304013694 Havana Radio Rebelde Network in Spanish 2300 
GMT 12 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL1304013694 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Radio Rebelde Network </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] On 12 April, Sugar Minister Nelson Torres stated 
that the remaining part of April is decisive for the sugarcane 
harvest and that we have to do everything possible, and more, to 
meet the production plan. He made this statement during a 
harvest emulation assessment over the last 10 days in the 
eastern provinces. Torres, who is also a member of the 
Politburo, added that the weather is helping; we therefore have 
to take advantage of it during the last 20 days of April and 
make the best effort in cutting and grinding with great 
efficiency. 

</TEXT>

