<H3> <TI>   Majority of Industries Set Prices in URV's </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Majority of Industries Set Prices in URV's </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PY1304020994 Brasilia Voz do Brasil Network in Portuguese 
2200 GMT 12 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> PY1304020994 </F>
<F P=104>  Brasilia Voz do Brasil Network </F>
<F P=105>  Portuguese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] According to a survey by the Sao Paulo State 
Federation of Industries, 82 percent of industrial companies 
already have converted their prices into Real Value Units, 
URV's. The survey was delivered today to Finance Ministry 
special adviser Milton Dallari. The survey also shows that 
nearly 40 percent of commercial stores already have set their 
prices in URV's. 
  Dallari, who today met with nearly 200 businessmen in Sao 
Paulo, said the government will institute the real only when all 
prices have been converted into URV's. Commenting on the 
conversion of utility rates, Dallari said that only the 
conversion of electricity and telephone rates will require an 
implementation decree, which will not be issued until June. 
Other utility rates will be converted into URV's by May. 

</TEXT>

