<F P=102>   PA1204153494 Mexico City Canal 13 Television Azteca Network 
in Spanish 1350 GMT 12 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA1204153494 </F>
<F P=104>  Mexico City Canal 13 Television Azteca Network 
in Spanish 1350 GMT 12 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=105> Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Enrique Gutierrez from the "Early Morning" </F>
newscast] 
  [Text] Nearly 100 members of the Party of the Democratic 
Revolution [PRD] have occupied the Coyuca de Benitez Municipal 
Office in Guerrero State to demand, among other things, clean 
municipal elections and lower water and electricity rates. 
  Members of the so-called Peasant Organization of the Sierra 
Madre of the South [Organizacion Campesina de la Sierra Madre 
del Sur], affiliated with the PRD, occupied the Coyuca de 
Benitez Municipal Office in Guerrero State on the morning of 11 
April. The PRD members, headed by Bartolo Guzman Martinez, held 
Mayor Jose Serna and four other municipal employees hostage. 
  Municipal Council Chairman Jesus Herrera Velez continues to 
work from a private home while the PRD members demand that he 
come to the municipal offices. The demonstrators are demanding 
fair municipal elections as well as a decrease in water and 
electricity rates. 

</TEXT>

