<H3> <TI>   Salinas Vows To Reverse Peasants' Isolation, Poverty </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Salinas Vows To Reverse Peasants' Isolation, Poverty </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA1204231294 Mexico City Canal 13 Television Azteca Network 
in Spanish 1300 GMT 11 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA1204231294 </F>
<F P=104>  Mexico City Canal 13 Television Azteca Network 
in Spanish 1300 GMT 11 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=105> Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "Early Morning" newscast] </F>
  [Text] In Morelos State on 10 April, Mexican President 
Carlos Salinas de Gortari presided over the 75th anniversary 
commemorating the death of southern caudillo Emiliano Zapata. 
  Thousands of peasants attended the commemoration. Salinas 
pledged to do more justice to the Mexican peasant sector and 
vowed to reverse the peasants' isolation and poverty. He said 
the ejido will be reinforced as the fundamental expression of 
social property in the country. 
  [Begin Salinas recording] We will do it, because Zapata's 
struggle is alive. Zapata lives and keeps fighting and demanding 
more justice, more respect, and more consideration for Mexican 
peasants. [end recording] 
  In Morelos, Zapata's birthplace, Salinas said changes to 
constitutional Article 27 meet the peasants' demand for legal 
ownership of their lands and freedom to work them. 
  [Begin Salinas recording] Large land owners will not 
reappear. They have already disappeared from our homeland's 
history. [end recording] 
  Salinas delivered checks for direct aid to peasants for the 
1993 to 1994 fall-winter crop cycle. Financial aid was 
delivered to 35,000 peasants throughout the country. Under the 
Prorural Areas Program, more than 100 million pesos have been 
doled out so far to assist 82,000 peasants. Salinas handed over 
ejido rights certificates and spoke about the agricultural 
sector's due loans, 70 percent of which will be refinanced with 
commercial banks. The president stressed the importance of 
these measures but admitted they are not enough. 
  [Begin Salinas recording] We must reverse the isolation and 
poverty we are still confronting in many rural areas. [end 
recording] 

</TEXT>

