<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Buenos Aires, 11 Apr (NA) -- The Justicialist Party 
[PJ] received nearly 38 percent of the vote nationwide in the 
elections for Constituent Assembly delegates, whereas the UCR 
[Radical Civic Union] vote dropped to 19.81 percent. The Grand 
Front displaced Modin [Movement for Dignity and Independence] in 
third place. 
  The following is the official tally following the tabulation 
of 97.68 percent of the polling stations nationwide: 


----------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
|Party             |Votes             |Percentage        |Delegates         | 
----------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
|PJ                |5,810,310         |37.72             |138               | 
----------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
|UCR               |3,051,973         |19.81             |74                | 
----------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
|Grand Front *     |1,972,112         |12.79             |31                | 
----------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
|Modin             |1,415,073         |9.18              |20                | 
----------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
|Republican Force  |275,986           |1.79              |7                 | 
----------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
|Progressive Democ-|255,599           |1.65              |3                 | 
|ratic Party       |                  |                  |                  | 
----------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
|UCeDe [Democratic |235,891           |1.53              |4                 | 
|Center Union]     |                  |                  |                  | 
----------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
|* The Grand Front is not considered a national party, but the total of the | 
|votes it received in the different constituencies where it fielded candida-| 
|tes adds up to 1,972,112. This enables it to send 31 delegates to the Cons-| 
|tituent Assembly.                                                          | 
----------------------------------------------------------------------------- 


