<F P=100> Venezuela </F>
<H3> <TI>   Disip Defuses Pipe Bomb Near Banco Latino </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Disip Defuses Pipe Bomb Near Banco Latino </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA1204171194 Caracas Venezolana de Television Network in 
Spanish 1604 GMT 12 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA1204171194 </F>
<F P=104>  Caracas Venezolana de Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Annerys Gonzalez; from "The News" newscast -- </F>
live relay] 
  [Text] Disip [Directorate of Intelligence and Prevention 
Services] members arrived at San Martin Avenue at 0910 [1310 
GMT] this Tuesday to defuse an alleged explosive found near a 
Banco Latino automatic teller machine. Well-protected members of 
the Disip Explosive Division are proceeding to defuse the pipe 
bomb. An official is signaling that the situation is under 
control. 
  As you can see, people were ordered out of the building to 
avoid any possible mishap. 
  Disip officials picked up a polyethylene bag--apparently 
containing an explosive device--and put it inside this truck to 
transport it to a location where it can be detonated. Members of 
the Special Action Brigade of the Judicial Technical Police 
[PTJ] and officials of the Disip Explosive Division arrived at 
the location to take pictures of the pipe bomb before it was 
detonated. 
  As you can see, all security measures are being taken to 
carry out this operation. Additionally, vehicle traffic in the 
area was stopped to prevent injury to people near the explosion 
site. We expect the detonation of the pipe bomb found at Banco 
Latino any minute. [loud explosion heard in background] 
  Vehicle traffic was finally resumed, and Disip officials 
departed the area. The Disip and PTJ will investigate this 
situation to determine who planted this explosive at Banco 
Latino in San Martin. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

