<H3> <TI>   Robaina Meets Argentina's Menem, Senators </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Robaina Meets Argentina's Menem, Senators </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   FL1404000494 Havana Radio Rebelde Network in Spanish 2300 
GMT 13 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL1404000494 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Radio Rebelde Network </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] A note from PRENSA LATINA says that Cuban Foreign 
Minister Roberto Robaina today received, in Buenos Aires, the 
Illustrious Visitor decoration which was granted to him by the 
deliberative council of the Argentine capital. The ceremony took 
place during a 48-hour visit by Robaina to Argentina during 
which he also met with the provisional president of the Senate, 
Eduardo Menem. 
  It has been reported that legislators from all the political 
parties represented in the Senate participated in this meeting, 
which has been described as friendly. Upon welcoming Roberto 
Robaina, Eduardo Menem ratified a resolution approved by the 
Senate last year in which the Senate came out in favor of a 
cessation of the U.S. blockade of Cuba. 

</TEXT>

