<F P=101> Cuba </F>
<H3> <TI>   Sugar Industry Minister Assesses Production </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Sugar Industry Minister Assesses Production </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   FL1304154694 Havana Radio Rebelde Network in Spanish 0900 
GMT 13 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL1304154694 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Radio Rebelde Network </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] After the latest control assessment in the country's 
western region, when Havana was declared the winner, Sugar 
Industry Minister Nelson Torres said the climate is favorable 
for making a maximum effort in cutting and grinding sugarcane 
with greater efficiency. 
  He said that Havana, Sancti Spiritus, and Cienfuegos are the 
provinces with the greatest possibilities for meeting the 
established plan before 1 May. He also urged all other provinces 
to set concrete goals for the international labor day. Nelson 
Torres explained the country's need to complete the planting of 
5,000 caballerias of sugarcane this month during the Spring 
campaign. 
  In the assessment by region, the western region has 
overpowered the eastern region, while Havana Province reached 
the best production level and was also one of the best in sugar 
production, sugarcane planting, and care of plantations. 

</TEXT>

