<H3> <TI>   Socialist Deputies Oppose Senate Article </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Socialist Deputies Oppose Senate Article </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   FL1304211594 Port-au-Prince Radio Metropole in French 1045 
GMT 13 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL1304211594 </F>
<F P=104>  Port-au-Prince Radio Metropole </F>
<F P=105>  French </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The leader of the socialist bloc in the Chamber of 
Deputies dissociates himself totally from the resolution passed 
by the Senate office led by Senator Sansaricq. The socialist 
bloc remains committed to the parliamentary plan regarding the 
unblocking of the Governors Island agreement, says Deputy Duly 
Brutus: 
  [Begin Brutus recording] We remain faithful to the plan 
which 
we ratified in the Chamber of Deputies in the Haitian 
parliament. We are waiting for the Senate's position with Sen. 
Firmin Jean-Louis; on the other hand, we feel that we must 
continue negotiating a solution to the Haitian political crisis. 
  [In Creole] The socialist bloc does not relate to this 
position on the application of Article 149 of the Constitution. 
We believe the time is not right to take such a step, mostly 
because we think that the parliament has made some progress on 
the international level. It would be a pity if today we were to 
take some false steps that would cause the parliament to lose 
the credibility it has on the international level. [end 
recording] 

</TEXT>

