<F P=100> Haiti </F>
<H3> <TI>   Gunfire Reported Between Army, Civilians </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Gunfire Reported Between Army, Civilians </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   FL1304210694 Port-au-Prince Signal FM Radio in French 1030 
GMT 13 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL1304210694 </F>
<F P=104>  Port-au-Prince Signal FM Radio </F>
<F P=105>  French </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Gunfire was exchanged during the night of 7 April 
between armed strangers and soldiers at the outpost of Borgne in 
northwest Haiti, sources reported in Port-au-Prince on 12 April. 
According to the sources, two military detachments from 
Cap-Haitien, 260 km north of Port-au-Prince, were sent to the 
area. Neither side suffered casualties. The unidentified 
attackers are being sought, according to a Haitian military 
source. Weapons of unrevealed nature and number were abandoned 
by the attackers, according to the same source. 
  A similar incident took place the night of 2 February in 
Chantal, near Les Cayes, 200 km south of Port-au-Prince. Two M-1 
rifles abandoned on that occasion by the attackers were 
recovered by soldiers. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
