<F P=100> Haiti </F>
<H3> <TI>   Anti-Drug Service, DEA Collaborate on Seizures </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Anti-Drug Service, DEA Collaborate on Seizures </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   FL1304184594 Port-au-Prince Signal FM Radio in French 1030 
GMT 13 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL1304184594 </F>
<F P=104>  Port-au-Prince Signal FM Radio </F>
<F P=105>  French </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Haitian Anti-Drug Service announced that it 
seized 12 kg of cocaine intended for the U.S. market at the 
Port-au-Prince International Airport on 12 April. The drug was 
concealed in the luggage of a Haitian citizen who was going to 
Miami, Florida, on a commercial flight. He was arrested and 
imprisoned. Two other people, who were with the owner of the 
luggage, were questioned. 
  In recent days, more than 60 kg of cocaine coming from 
Colombia and intended for the U.S. market has been seized in 
Port-au-Prince by the Haitian Anti-Drug Service, which is 
working jointly with the local branch of the U.S. anti-drug 
office, Drug Enforcement Agency [DEA] [previous four words in 
English]. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

