<F P=100> MEXICO </F>
<H3> <TI>   PRI Officials Appointed to New Positions </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    PRI Officials Appointed to New Positions </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA1304035894 Mexico City XEW Television Network in Spanish 
0430 GMT 12 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA1304035894 </F>
<F P=104>  Mexico City XEW Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "24 Hours" newscast] </F>
  [Text] Three changes were made within the PRI 
[Institutional Revolutionary Party] on 11 April. Mr. Lievano 
Saenz Ortiz left the Secretariat of Information and Propaganda 
to become the private secretary of PRI presidential candidate 
Ernesto Zedillo. Lievano Saenz has held several posts in the 
government. He was a senior officer at the Secretariat of 
Social Development, director of property and furnishings of the 
defunct Secretariat of Urban Development and Ecology, and 
general director of the Panamericana Sulphur Company [Azufrera 
Panamericana] and the Istmo Exploration Company. 
  The PRI's new secretary of information and propaganda is Mr. 
Carlos Salomon Camara, formerly the Federal District's secretary 
general of social development, a political delegate in Coyoacan, 
and commercial director of Fertimex [Mexican Fertilizers]. He 
has been a PRI member for 19 years and is a columnist for the 
newspaper EXCELSIOR and the magazine SIEMPRE. 
  Mr. Esteban Moctezuma Barragan will hold the newly created 
post of first adjunct secretary; he was a senior officer at the 
Secretariat of Programming and Budget, a senior officer at the 
Secretariat of Public Education and, until recently, deputy 
secretary of public education. 
  These appointments were disclosed by Mr. Fernando Ortiz 
Arana, president of the PRI's National Executive Committee, who 
swore in the three new appointees. Mr. Ortiz Arana stated the 
following about the three appointees: 
  [Begin Ortiz recording] They will give credit to the rules 
that have governed their conduct in the many positions they have 
held. They have personal and political honesty, integrity, 
intelligence, and a determination to serve foremost the causes 
of the Mexican people. [end recording] 
  The brief ceremony was also attended by Mr. Ignacio Pichardo 
Pagaza, the recently appointed PRI secretary general. 

</TEXT>

