<F P=100> Nicaragua </F>
<H3> <TI>   Godoy, Ortega Oppose Economic Measures </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Godoy, Ortega Oppose Economic Measures </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA1404025494 Managua Radio Nicaragua Network in Spanish 1200 
GMT 11 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA1404025494 </F>
<F P=104>  Managua Radio Nicaragua Network </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "This Morning" newscast] </F>
  [Text] Nicaraguan Vice President Virgilio Godoy Reyes this 
weekend agreed with Daniel Ortega's opposition to the national 
economy adjustment agreement. On Sunday, Godoy Reyes and 
Daniel Ortega both said on local radio stations that street 
violence may erupt if the government implements the economic 
measures scheduled for this month. Godoy, however, did not say 
whether UNO [National Opposition Union] will support such 
protests. The Sandinist National Liberation Front, which has 
always supported violence, says it will support these events. 
  Ortega and Godoy agreed the economic measures are very harsh 
and might prompt disturbances. The leadership of COSEP [Higher 
Council of Private Enterprise], through its president Ramiro 
Gurdian, said the measures should be implemented as the only 
real solution to Nicaragua's economic problems. 

</TEXT>

