  [Text] Presidency Minister Antonio Lacayo said on Friday 
that the implementation of economic adjustment measures will 
provide financing for the agriculture and production sectors. 
Lacayo, while visiting several communities in La Trinidad, 
Esteli Department, where he inaugurated several projects, said 
the agreement with the IMF should definitely be signed. Lacayo 
has said on previous occasions that with or without the support 
of the Sandinist National Liberation Front, the adjustment 
agreement should be implemented. He has also characterized 
Daniel Ortega's objections as political populism. 

