<F P=101> Argentina </F>
<H3> <TI>   PLO To Open Bureau in Buenos Aires </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    PLO To Open Bureau in Buenos Aires </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PY1304232594 Buenos Aires CLARIN in Spanish 13 Apr 94 p 16 </F>
<F P=103> PY1304232594 </F>
<F P=104>  Buenos Aires CLARIN </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] Foreign Ministry sources informed CLARIN on 12 
April that, pursuant to an agreement reached on 12 April in 
Tunisia between Foreign Minister Guido Di Tella and Palestinian 
leader Yasir 'Arafat, the Palestinian Liberation Organization 
(PLO) will open "an affairs bureau" in Buenos Aires within a few 
months. 
  According to the talks held on 12 April between Di Tella and 
'Arafat, when the PLO achieves statehood, thanks to the historic 
peace agreements between the Israelis and Palestinians, the 
bureau may become an embassy, with the appropriate powers. 
  The establishment of an "affairs bureau," a diplomatic 
status 
below that of an embassy, has been an old goal of the Arab 
community in Argentina. After President Carlos Menem -- of 
Syrian ancestry -- was inaugurated in 1989, the Arab community 
in Argentina again favored this measure. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

