  [Text] Buenos Aires, 13 Apr (NA) -- Cuban Foreign Minister 
Roberto Robaina stressed this afternoon that the debt his 
country has not yet settled with Argentina "is not an issue that 
has been frozen." In this regard, he expressed his government's 
willingness to seek alternative repayment methods. 
  The diplomat, who is paying a 48-hour official visit to 
Argentina, also denied negotiations for a meeting between 
President Carlos Menem and Cuban leader Fidel Castro during an 
upcoming Ibero-American summit in Cartagena de Indias. 
  In remarks made in the Senate, Robaina added: "The 
possibilities are always open. It depends on the activities 
each one of them has during the summit. My visit's goal, 
however, is not to prepare a meeting. Thus far, there is 
nothing on this issue." 

</TEXT>

