<F P=104>  Panama City Circuito RPC Radio </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Interview with Panamanian Education Minister Marcos Alarcon </F>
by reporter Luis Alberto Jimenez at the Palace of the Herons in 
Panama City on 14 April--recorded] 
  [Text] [Alarcon] We all were watching, let's say, what the 
television stations were analyzing. Nothing at all was being 
planned. We were simple viewers analyzing the various reactions 
as reflected by the television interviews. 
  [Jimenez] Did the members of the Cabinet Council know of the 
content of the document that was going to be presented? 
  [Alarcon] No Cabinet Council member knew about this 
document. 
This was a decision made solely by the president, and if you 
listen to the documentary introduction the president himself 
assumes the responsibility of the content of the document. 
  [Jimenez] Politically speaking, who gains from this? 
  [Alarcon] The people are the ones who benefit. The people 
are the ones who did not know the inside details of how the 
military government operated. 

</TEXT>

