<F P=100> Chile </F>
<H3> <TI>   PRC Defense Minister Meets With Pinochet </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    PRC Defense Minister Meets With Pinochet </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PY1404205094 Santiago Television Nacional de Chile Imagen 
Internacional in Spanish 1800 GMT 14 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> PY1404205094 </F>
<F P=104>  Santiago Television Nacional de Chile Imagen 
Internacional </F>

<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Today, the second day of his official visit to 
Chile, PRC Defense Minister Chi Haotian met with Army Commander 
General Augusto Pinochet. 
  Colonel Chi Haotian is responsible for one of the largest 
armed forces in the world. The PRC land, sea, and air forces 
comprise more than 10 million soldiers. 
  Chi Haotian came to Chile in response to an invitation by 
the 
Defense Ministry and met with Chilean Army Commander Gen. 
Augusto Pinochet. The PRC minister is accompanied by seven 
high-ranking PRC People's Liberation Army members. The two 
military commanders introduced each other to their respective 
successors [as heard] and exchanged gifts, after which they held 
a 25-minute meeting. 
  One of Chi Haotian's most important activities in Chile will 
take place this afternoon when he will visit the FAMAE [Army 
Ordnance]. There is a chance the PRC will want to purchase 
Chilean-made war materiel. 

</TEXT>

