<F P=106> [From the "Telemetro Reports" newscast] </F>
  [Text] Seven hours before the awaited presidential 
announcement, President Endara has again asked the Panamanian 
people to be patient. He neither confirmed nor denied that the 
announcement he will make tonight is linked to fellow party 
members' involvement in a scandal involving duty free stores. 
  [Begin recording] [Unidentified reporter] Is the 
announcement 
you will make tonight linked to members of your party being 
involved in the contraband scandal? 
  [Endara] I am not going to discuss that subject now. Please 
be patient, you only have to wait seven hours. 
  [Reporter] Is the situation so critical that you have called 
a special council [consejo extraordinario] meeting minutes or 
hours before the announcement? 
  [Endara] Yes, I thought it was advisable, and therefore I 
called a meeting yesterday. It was initially scheduled for 
1600, but I had to postpone it until 1700 due to a last minute 
appointment. 
  [Reporter] Is all this related to the announcement you will 
make tonight? 
  [Endara] Yes, it has to do with the announcement. 
  [Reporter] Will they accompany you? 
  [Endara] Yes, they will accompany me. [end recording] 

</TEXT>

