<F P=100> Paraguay </F>
<H3> <TI>   `Terrorist' Plans To Poison Israeli Beef Derailed </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    `Terrorist' Plans To Poison Israeli Beef Derailed </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PY1404200194 Asuncion ABC COLOR in Spanish 14 Apr 94 p 90 </F>
<F P=103> PY1404200194 </F>
<F P=104>  Asuncion ABC COLOR </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] The Shiite terrorist who came to our country 
intended not only to attack Israeli diplomatic headquarters 
here, but also to poison Israelis in the Middle East as well. 
To achieve this, he planned to gain access to large shipments 
of beef earmarked for Israel in order to poison them with a 
powerful toxic substance. 
  This warning was announced by the Israeli intelligence 
service soon after it informed the Paraguayan National Police 
that Ahmad al-Maqdaf, a fundamentalist Shiite, had arrived here 
a month ago. 
  Police Superintendent Enrique de Jesus Martinetti, director 
of the National Police Intelligence Department, confirmed this 
report and noted that the information was provided by the 
Israeli secret service. 
  The terrorist had to locate meat-packing plants that export 
meat to Israel, find a way to gain access to the products, and 
then poison them with a deadly toxic substance. 
  The consequences would have been devastating. The objective 
was to kill hundreds of Israelis in important cities in their 
country. 
  The name of the meat-packing plants are "Frigobeef," located 
in Capitan Lombardo close to Artigas, and "San Antonio" in the 
city of the same name. 
  Intelligence Department personnel went to those meat-packing 
plants and warned the managers to take the necessary precautions 
by not allowing strangers on their premises, thereby foiling any 
sabotage attempts. 
  Martinetti noted that the meat was imported by a private -- 
not government-owned -- Israeli meat-packing plant. 
  He said: "We were alerted by the Israelis and are now 
conducting inquiries. We have been informed that this Shiite, 
Ahmad al-Maqdaf, intended to poison a large shipment of beef 
that was going to Israel. We have apparently foiled this 
attempt with the help of the Israelis. Al-Maqdaf has been 
already seen in Lebanon." [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS4-10653 </DOCNO>
