<H3> <TI>   Fujimori States 3d Guzman Letter `Under Lock' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Fujimori States 3d Guzman Letter `Under Lock' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PY1404155494 Lima Global de Television Network in Spanish 
0130 GMT 14 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> PY1404155494 </F>
<F P=104>  Lima Global de Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] President Alberto Fujimori announced today that he 
has a third letter from Shining Path leader Abimael Guzman and 
he will reveal the letter at the appropriate time. Fujimori 
also denied that a letter published in a local magazine is true. 
  [Begin recording] [Fujimori] [words indistinct] Second, I am 
keeping the third letter under lock, in a safe, and no one else 
knows the combination. I therefore do not see how the letter 
could have left my safe. Then [words indistinct] the magazine 
published a letter which is not the third letter. I deny it. 
  [Unidentified reporter] [words indistinct] 
  [Fujimori] [words indistinct] Look, here we must use 
censorship to be able to handle properly the psychological 
aspect in the struggle against the Shining Path. The handling 
of this has been good. Now no one can criticize me about why 
the letter was published or that it was a propaganda coup for 
the Shining Path. All the facts contravene this statement 
because, thanks to the way the famous letters of Guzman were 
handled, massive desertions took place -- not hundreds, but 
thousands of Shining Path members deserted. The study we made 
from the psychological point of view was correct. [end 
recording] 

