<F P=100> Venezuela </F>
<H3> <TI>   Senate Approves Special Powers for President </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Senate Approves Special Powers for President </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA1404192494 Hamburg DPA in Spanish 1853 GMT 14 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> PA1404192494 </F>
<F P=104>  Hamburg DPA </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Caracas, 14 Apr (DPA)--The Venezuelan Senate today 
approved the so-called Special Powers Act, granting special 
powers to President Rafael Caldera to decree economic and 
financial measures. 
  This law will give Caldera special powers to legislate, a 
function that basically belongs to the Congress. 
  The Special Powers Act was proposed to implement legislative 
initiatives pertaining to income tax, general sales and excise 
taxes, tax reform, bank debit tax, the Stamp Tax Law, and the 
Concessions Law. 

</TEXT>

