<H3> <TI>   Lage, Torres Attend Harvest Evaluation Meetings </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Lage, Torres Attend Harvest Evaluation Meetings </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   FL1504012994 Havana Radio Rebelde Network in Spanish 2300 
GMT 14 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL1504012994 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Radio Rebelde Network </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Camaguey correspondent Lucilo Tejera] </F>
  [Text] In Camaguey, Nelson Torres, member of the Politburo 
and sugar industry minister, has issued a call to those 
participating in the current sugar harvest to make a greater 
effort during this phase of the harvest. April is very important 
to the objective of increasing the quantities of raw product 
produced, and May must be the month in which operations are 
concluded, although a number of mills may continue to grind in 
June, said Torres during an analysis of the harvest in Camaguey, 
Las Tunas, and Holguin. 
  He stressed that a greater effort is necessary on the days 
when there is activity, and pointed out that it would be a good 
idea to increase the direct transportation of cane from the 
fields where it is being harvested to the mills. He also called 
attention to the fact that it is indispensable to apply 
alternatives at each place to reduce dependency on electric 
power provided by the national system, because during recent 
working days, collection centers were affected by interruptions 
in electric service. 
  During the analysis meeting, which was presided over by 
Carlos Lage, member of the Politburo and secretary of the 
executive committee of the Council of Ministers, it was reported 
that Las Tunas obtained the best results in principal indicators 
during the period 1-10 April, pushing Camaguey into second 
place. Camaguey had been in first place. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

